      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a good start, but it's a bit too academic/vague. Can you expand on the second point? I want to make sure the essay doesn't just sound like a list of facts, but actually hits hard on why the current \"meritocracy\" system is basically a lie when it comes to race. Like, how can I argue that the idea of \"working hard to get ahead\" is just a way to ignore the systemic stuff? Use some really strong language to show why the old way of thinking is fundamentally broken.",
